I wanted to give them the benefit of the doubt because it was a super busy day for them I had seen the line by the door! So, I tried to place another mobile order and let me tell you I was upset because now this has happened to me not once not twice but three times at this location. SOLUTION :  Now, I understand the place gets extremely busy, but they should have someone focused on the mobile orders while another is focused on the clients on line. P.S.: I love the location, it is a nice store, just needs a few staff adjustments.

This is a new location so everything is in great working order. Some older locations will have problems with their soda machine and haveshaky chairs that's not the case here. But their lines are slower than usual. That's to be expected with a new location finding it's way. I have been here twice ordered the same burrito and it's been inconsistent.

I was so excited to come here as I love chipotle (and finally there was one near me)! But the staff here are not great (and I’ve never had this problem at a chipotle).  On the first visit I noticed the price we were charged didn’t match what the menu listed. When I brought it up to the manager he was extremely defensive and I had to explain the math to him several times before he finally realized the mistake. He eventually conceded that the menu pricing was incorrect and credited us back, but still it didn’t seem fair to everyone else who was being overcharged (people expect to pay the listed price)! As a side note, the corn was so cold it hurt my teeth.  On a separate occasion my boyfriend went and the girl serving him was so out of it (in his words, stoned) that she tried wrapping up his bowl before he even got to the sour cream/salsa station.  UPDATE: I had a wonderful experience with a different manager and another wonderful server!
